@@ -15,7 +15,11 @@

 **Fixed**

- - Nothing yet!
+ - `@Headers` annotation now throws `IllegalArgumentException` at service creation time for
+   header strings that are missing a colon or have an empty header name (e.g., `"BearerToken123"`).
+   Previously these produced a generic validation error; now the message explicitly identifies the
+   missing colon or empty name. This is a **potential breaking change** if your code relied on the
+   old error message text or on malformed header strings being silently accepted.


